		<item>
		<title>Finance Leaders Warn Over Risks of Mythos AI Model</title>
		<link>https://ventureburn.com/finance-leaders-warn-over-risks-of-mythos-ai-model/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Ekemini]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Fri, 17 Apr 2026 17:56:20 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Venture Capital]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ventureburn.com/?p=200124</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Global financial stability is facing a &#8220;new and unprecedented&#8221; threat, according to a chorus of international finance ministers and central bankers gathered this week for the IMF and World Bank</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/finance-leaders-warn-over-risks-of-mythos-ai-model/" data-wpel-link="internal">Finance Leaders Warn Over Risks of Mythos AI Model</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Global financial stability is facing a &#8220;new and unprecedented&#8221; threat, according to a chorus of international finance ministers and central bankers gathered this week for the IMF and World Bank spring meetings. The source of their anxiety is not a failing economy or a geopolitical conflict, but a specific artificial intelligence model: Claude Mythos, the latest &#8220;frontier&#8221; model developed by the San Francisco-based firm </span><a href="https://www.anthropic.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Anthropic</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">In a series of urgent briefings and public statements on Friday, April 17, 2026, leaders, including Bank of England Governor Andrew Bailey and U.S. Treasury Secretary Scott Bessent warned that the Mythos model represents a qualitative leap in AI capabilities that could systematically dismantle current financial cybersecurity defences.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">An &#8220;Unknown Unknown&#8221;</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The alarm was first triggered earlier this month when Anthropic took the unusual step of delaying the model&#8217;s full public release. The company’s internal testing revealed that Mythos possesses an &#8220;unprecedented ability&#8221; to identify and exploit thousands of high-severity software vulnerabilities, including &#8220;zero-day&#8221; flaws that have survived decades of human and automated scrutiny in every major operating system and web browser.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_200125" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200125" class="size-large wp-image-200125" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/AI-3-1024x853.jpg" alt="AI" width="1024" height="853" /><p id="caption-attachment-200125" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Unsplash</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;The issue we are facing with Anthropic is that it is an &#8216;unknown unknown&#8217;,&#8221; said Canadian Finance Minister François-Philippe Champagne during a BBC interview in Washington. &#8220;It requires a level of attention and safeguards we haven&#8217;t seen since the dawn of the nuclear age to ensure the resiliency of our financial system.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The model’s performance has reportedly stunned regulators. In a test conducted by the UK’s AI Security Institute (AISI), Mythos successfully completed a complex, 32-step autonomous cyberattack simulation, a task that typically takes elite human hackers days to perform with no human intervention.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/expo-secures-45m-and-unveils-new-expo-agent-tool/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Expo Secures $45M and Unveils New Expo Agent Tool</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Banks Scramble to Patch Defenses</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The threat to &#8220;systemically important&#8221; financial institutions, banks whose collapse could trigger a global depression, has moved to the top of the international agenda. Last week, U.S. Treasury Secretary Scott Bessent summoned the CEOs of America&#8217;s largest banks to a closed-door meeting to discuss the &#8220;offensive cyber capabilities&#8221; of Mythos.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Goldman Sachs CEO David Solomon confirmed he is &#8220;hyper-aware&#8221; of the risks. &#8220;We are working closely with Anthropic and our security vendors to harness these frontier capabilities for defence before they can be used for offence,&#8221; Solomon told analysts.</span></p>
<p><a href="https://ventureburn.com/anthropic-engages-eu-on-cybersecurity-ai-models/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Anthropic </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">is currently operating under a protocol called &#8216;Project Glasswing&#8217;, limiting access to the Mythos model to roughly 40 vetted organizations, including JPMorgan Chase, Apple, and Microsoft. This &#8220;vetted-only&#8221; approach allows these institutions to use the model to find and patch their own vulnerabilities before malicious actors can develop similar AI-driven tools.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">The Governance Gap</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Despite the defensive efforts, European Central Bank President Christine Lagarde warned that the current global governance framework is woefully inadequate. &#8220;We have a responsible company in Anthropic acting with restraint today,&#8221; Lagarde told Bloomberg TV, &#8220;but if these capabilities fall into the wrong hands tomorrow, there is no international framework in place to manage those things. We need to work on that immediately.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Bank of England Governor Andrew Bailey echoed the sentiment, noting that regulators are trapped in a race against time. &#8220;If you go too early with rules, you risk distorting evolution,&#8221; Bailey said. &#8220;If you go too late, things get out of control.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">As the spring meetings conclude, the IMF has signalled that AI cybersecurity will be &#8220;absolutely essential&#8221; on the international agenda for the remainder of 2026. For now, the financial world remains in a state of high alert, racing to repair the very digital foundations that the Mythos model has proven to be unexpectedly fragile.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/finance-leaders-warn-over-risks-of-mythos-ai-model/" data-wpel-link="internal">Finance Leaders Warn Over Risks of Mythos AI Model</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
			</item>
