		<title>Expo Secures $45M and Unveils New Expo Agent Tool</title>
		<link>https://ventureburn.com/expo-secures-45m-and-unveils-new-expo-agent-tool/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Ekemini]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Fri, 17 Apr 2026 16:22:06 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Venture Capital]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ventureburn.com/?p=200119</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Today, Expo (650 Industries Inc.), the open-source giant behind the React Native community, announced that it just closed a $45M Series B. The round was led by Georgian. As Expo</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/expo-secures-45m-and-unveils-new-expo-agent-tool/" data-wpel-link="internal">Expo Secures $45M and Unveils New Expo Agent Tool</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Today, </span><a href="https://expo.dev/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Expo </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">(650 Industries Inc.), the open-source giant behind the React Native community, announced that it just closed a $45M Series B. The </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/zum-raises-100m-to-expand-connected-mobility-platform/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">round </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">was led by Georgian. As Expo enters what it calls its &#8216;agentic&#8217; era, it&#8217;s targeting closing the widening divide between AI-generated code and production-native apps.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The round brought in solid traction from new and existing investors (including Leadout Capital, A.Capital Ventures and Red Swan Ventures). With the new inflow of capital, Expo intends to expedite developing its infrastructure as a service offering and directly embed super-intelligent AI functionalities into the developer workflow.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Solving the &#8220;Last Mile&#8221; of AI Development</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Writing code has become quicker due to tools such as GitHub Copilot and ChatGPT, but the transformation of this code into an actual, high-performance mobile application still remains a hard, broken process. Charlie Cheever, co-founder and CEO of Expo, told me, &#8220;AI is spitballing snippets, but business-critical apps are not making it to production&#8221; due to native integrations, builds, and store submissions.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_200120" style="width: 410px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200120" class="wp-image-200120" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Expo.jpg" alt="Expo logo" width="400" height="113" /><p id="caption-attachment-200120" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Expo</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To remedy this, Expo launched Expo Agent, the first AI for the mobile lifecycle, ever publicly previewing it as part of the second version of its CLI. This AI is, in essence, an &#8220;embedded solutions engineer&#8221;, a multimodal agent that, unlike general LLMs, has a comprehensive knowledge of the relevant platform-specific patterns, configs, and constraints of iOS and Android development, among others.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Cheever explained, &#8220;We constructed the platform for mobile apps, and now we can embed that into Expo Agent.&#8221; He continued to state that &#8220;Our goal is to empower all builders, whether they are a single person or a 30,000-person enterprise, with the fastest possible route to production quality.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/zum-raises-100m-to-expand-connected-mobility-platform/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Zum Raises $100M to Expand Connected Mobility Platform</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">A New Chapter for the React Native Ecosystem</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Although funding arrives during a period of incredible growth for Expo. The platform has around 4 million weekly downloads and is the basis of the rich applications that are used by millions from Pizza Hut, Phantom and the New York MTA.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Additionally, Expo revealed the hire of Seth Webster as chief developer evangelist. A known figure in the developer community, Webster will spearhead the company&#8217;s initiative to educate developers on moving towards an AI-native development paradigm.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Strategic Roadmap: Speed and Integration</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The $45 million will be deployed across three primary areas:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Platform Acceleration</b><span style="font-weight: 400">: Faster EAS speeds for quicker cloud builds and updates.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Agentic Tooling</b><span style="font-weight: 400">: Moving the currently BETA Expo Agent into the core of the developer experience by iterating on it fast.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Enterprise Growth</b><span style="font-weight: 400">: Regarding enterprise growth, they are one of the top-tier security and performance mobile development frameworks, assisting their growing network of Fortune 500 companies in migrating their mobile stack to React Native.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">According to Emily Walsh, Lead Investor at Georgian, &#8220;A lot [of investment] then followed in Expo because we saw that this was an inflection point for them, that they moved from being a framework to being the infrastructure layer, and that thanks to this boom of AI-assisted coding, they&#8217;re democratizing the way in which applications are built and maintained at scale.&#8221;</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/expo-secures-45m-and-unveils-new-expo-agent-tool/" data-wpel-link="internal">Expo Secures $45M and Unveils New Expo Agent Tool</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
			</item>
		<item>
		<title>Nas.Com Secures $27M for AI Creator Economy Growth</title>
		<link>https://ventureburn.com/nas-com-secures-27m-for-ai-creator-economy-growth/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Ekemini]]></dc:creator>
