					<description><![CDATA[<p>Zenskar Raised $15 Million To Advance AI Finance Automation Zenskar has raised $15 million in Series A funding led by Susquehanna Venture Capital. The round also featured participation from Bessemer Venture Partners,</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/zenskar-raises-15m-ai-billing-platform/" data-wpel-link="internal">Zenskar Raises $15 Million To Expand AI Billing Automation Platform</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Zenskar Raised $15 Million To Advance AI Finance Automation</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Zenskar has raised $15 million in Series A funding led by Susquehanna Venture Capital. The round also featured participation from Bessemer Venture Partners, Shine Capital and Rho. Other backers including Rocketship, J-Ventures and Converge also participated in the round.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The financing is a significant milestone for the AI-native billing platform. Zenskar specializes in revenue automation for complex B2B business models&#8221;. The company is building a system designed to remove manual finance processes across modern enterprises.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Zenskar plans to use the capital to expand its agentic capabilities. These include automation tools across billing, collections and revenue recognition. The goal is to support finance teams dealing with increasingly complex pricing structures.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company believes traditional finance systems cannot handle modern workflows. Legacy platforms were built for simpler subscription models. Today’s pricing structures require more flexible and </span><a href="https://www.algotive.ai/blog/intelligent-systems-what-are-they-how-do-they-work-and-why-are-they-so-important" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">intelligent systems</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">.</span></p>
<h2><b>AI-Native Platform Targets Complex B2B Pricing Models</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Modern B2B companies operate with highly complex pricing structures. These include usage-based billing, prepaid credits and contract amendments. Many also operate across multiple entities and currencies.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Legacy billing systems struggle to manage this level of complexity. Finance teams often rely on workarounds and manual processes. This creates risks such as revenue leakage and delayed collections.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Zenskar addresses these challenges with a flexible data model. It represents contracts as structured objects rather than rigid templates. This allows the system to adapt to changing pricing models without disruption.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The platform also integrates rule-based calculations with AI automation. This ensures accuracy and compliance across financial workflows. Finance teams gain more control while reducing operational effort.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Zenskar’s approach focuses on building from the ground up. Instead of adding AI to outdated systems, it uses an AI-native architecture. This creates a stronger foundation for automation and scalability.</span></p>
<h2><b>Agentic Architecture Enables Zero-Touch Finance Workflows<br />
</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_200114" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200114" class="size-full wp-image-200114" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/create-a-futuristic-neon-lit-visualizati_cyF3IsTbSVmNUZiSkuj7Bg_RTOsmHDlRoeIpIQmfUsJ1A_cover_hd.png" alt="AI finance platform using autonomous agents to automate billing, collections, and financial workflows without manual input." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-200114" class="wp-caption-text">Zenskar’s agentic architecture enables Zero-Touch Finance, automating complex workflows and improving efficiency across modern finance operations. Source: Created by Ventureburn</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">A core feature of Zenskar’s platform is its agentic architecture. This includes a growing Agents Marketplace. Finance teams can create and deploy agents across workflows without engineering support.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">These agents handle tasks across the order-to-cash cycle. This includes billing, revenue recognition and collections. Teams can customise agents to match specific business rules and processes.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Zenskar also offers integrations with workplace tools such as Slack. Teams can assign tasks, review exceptions and approve actions directly within these environments. This reduces friction in daily operations.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The system introduces the concept of Zero-Touch Finance. This model removes the need for manual interaction with financial tools. Instead, intelligent agents manage processes based on predefined rules.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Zenskar has reported strong growth in platform adoption. The company achieved five times revenue growth over the past year. Customers report faster billing cycles and improved financial accuracy.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The platform is already used across multiple industries. Businesses benefit from reduced operational workload. They also gain better visibility into financial performance and revenue streams.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: <a href="https://ventureburn.com/loop-raises-95m-ai-supply-chain-platform/" data-wpel-link="internal">Loop Raises $95 Million To Strengthen AI Supply Chain Platform</a></span></p>
<h2><b>Funding Supports Expansion Across Enterprise Finance Use Cases</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The new funding will support expansion across additional enterprise use cases. Zenskar aims to broaden its platform capabilities. This includes deeper automation across financial operations.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company will invest in product development and engineering. It also plans to grow its team to support increasing demand. Expanding AI capabilities remains a key priority.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Zenskar is targeting a growing market for AI-driven finance tools. Investors are increasingly focused on back-office automation. These systems offer strong value through efficiency and cost reduction.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Finance teams have traditionally been slower to adopt AI. This is due to strict requirements around accuracy and compliance. Zenskar’s architecture aims to address these concerns directly.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company’s flexible system allows businesses to scale without adding headcount. It supports complex pricing models without requiring custom development. This creates a strong advantage in a competitive market.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Zenskar aims to become a foundational platform for modern finance operations. Its focus on automation and flexibility positions it for continued growth. The Series A funding strengthens its ability to execute this vision.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/zenskar-raises-15m-ai-billing-platform/" data-wpel-link="internal">Zenskar Raises $15 Million To Expand AI Billing Automation Platform</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
