					<description><![CDATA[<p>Loop Secures Major Investment To Advance Supply Chain AI Loop has raised $95 million in a new Series C funding round. The investment was led by Valor Equity Partners and</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/loop-raises-95m-ai-supply-chain-platform/" data-wpel-link="internal">Loop Raises $95 Million To Strengthen AI Supply Chain Platform</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Loop Secures Major Investment To Advance Supply Chain AI</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Loop has raised $95 million in a new Series C funding round. The investment was led by Valor Equity Partners and the Valor Atreides AI Fund. Additional participation came from 8VC, Founders Fund, Index Ventures, J.P. Morgan Growth Equity Partners, and Tao Capital Partners. The round strengthens Loop’s position as a rising force in AI-driven supply chain intelligence.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The raise arrives during a period of global disruption within logistics. Companies continue to deal with tariffs, higher energy costs, and shifting supplier dynamics. Many rely on legacy systems that make data hard to access. Operational decisions often rely on incomplete information, creating higher risk across supply chains.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Loop aims to solve these issues with a verticalised AI platform. It focuses on structuring trapped operational data. This includes </span><a href="https://www.igi-global.com/dictionary/fragmented-information-sources/11478" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">fragmented information</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> stored across disconnected systems. The company believes enterprises need a more trustworthy data foundation. Better structure supports faster decisions and improved working capital management.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company plans to use the funds to deepen product capabilities. It will also expand engineering teams and invest in AI talent. Loop wants to address a broader set of enterprise use cases. This includes deeper integrations across financial, operational, and logistics systems.</span></p>
<h2><b>Loop Tackles Fragmented Supply Chain Data With Structured Intelligence</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Supply chains are among the most challenging environments in which to deploy AI. Much of the data is either inconsistent or is stored in inaccessible formats. Many businesses depend on documents like PDFs, emails, paper trails and obsolete digital files. This leads to blind spots in proc-ess visibility at both work and long-term planning levels.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Loop solves these problems by creating a structured intelligence layer. It transforms unstructured documents into usable data. This information is then used to power workflows in finance, logistics, and compliance. The company focuses first on back-office functions where information is most fragmented. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">These areas also have the highest financial impact. By structuring data and automating related processes Loop helps companies reduce cost. It also improves visibility across their networks. This gives enterprises clearer insight into cost-to-serve and operational performance. Better visibility allows teams to take quicker action in volatile moments.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Loop’s platform is expanding across additional data types. These include supplier, trade, warehouse, procurement, and inbound logistics data. The platform also strengthens connections across ERP, TMS, WMS and order-management systems. Each integration builds a more complete view of the supply chain.</span></p>
<h2><b>DUX AI Models Strengthen Decision-Making Across Enterprise Workflows<br />
</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_200109" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200109" class="size-full wp-image-200109" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/create-a-futuristic-neon-lit-visualizati_d_YoVUZWSzmj9PD8D_7Saw_mTXg5N4eRVq1aIEA3cxQIg_cover_hd-1.png" alt="AI logistics platform analyzing supply chain data to deliver predictive insights and improve operational efficiency." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-200109" class="wp-caption-text">Loop’s DUX AI system transforms fragmented logistics data into actionable insights, enabling smarter decisions and resilient supply chain operations. Source: Created by Ventureburn</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">At the centre of Loop’s platform is DUX. This family of models and agents is built specifically for logistics environments. DUX combines document understanding, data analysis, and domain expertise. It helps ingest, standardise, contextualise, and execute decisions on logistics data.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The system offers a unified view of operational information. This view improves automation across complex processes. DUX supports decision-making by giving teams consistent, clean data. These capabilities help businesses streamline operations and reduce manual workload.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Loop customers include brands across healthcare, food services, retail, and consumer goods. These companies use Loop to improve visibility and reduce operational risk. The platform helps teams understand where costs appear. It also highlights areas vulnerable to delays or inefficiencies.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">DUX brings predictive capabilities into the platform. It does more than identify issues. It also highlights actions companies can take to strengthen logistics. This includes building resilience against external shocks such as delays, demand swings, or supplier disruptions.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Loop believes these features will set a new standard for logistics intelligence. AI will become central to how enterprises manage supply chain decisions. By creating a structured data foundation Loop positions itself at the centre of this shift.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: <a href="https://ventureburn.com/slash-financial-raises-100m-ai-banking-platform/" data-wpel-link="internal">Slash Financial Raises $100 Million To Expand AI Banking Platform</a></span></p>
<h2><b>New Funding Accelerates Expansion Across Key Supply Chain Functions</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The new investment will help Loop broaden its industry reach. The company wants to support more enterprise use cases. This includes deeper interactions across operational and financial workflows. The goal is to become the intelligence layer that guides supply chain decisions.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Loop will also grow its team across engineering, AI, and customer operations. The company believes this will strengthen product velocity. It also supports innovation across logistics and automation. More talent will help Loop focus on predictive capabilities that guide forward-looking decisions.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company’s founders expect rapid adoption in the coming years. Many enterprises now face unpredictable operating environments. Those that invest early in structured intelligence will gain long-term advantages. Loop believes this shift will help define the next decade of logistics and supply chain transformation.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company’s platform began in freight audit and payment. It has since expanded into a larger enterprise intelligence system. This expansion reflects growing demand for unified supply chain data. Businesses want tighter control over cost, visibility, and working capital. Loop plans to address each of these priorities as its platform grows.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The Series C round gives Loop the resources to scale quickly. It aims to help companies turn fragmented information into strategic action. The long-term goal is to support resilience across global supply chains. This approach positions Loop as a key platform for operational intelligence.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/loop-raises-95m-ai-supply-chain-platform/" data-wpel-link="internal">Loop Raises $95 Million To Strengthen AI Supply Chain Platform</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
