					<description><![CDATA[<p>Slash Financial Reaches Unicorn Status With $100 Million Raise Slash Financial just pulled in $100 million in its Series C, with Ribbit Capital leading the way. Now, the company’s worth</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/slash-financial-raises-100m-ai-banking-platform/" data-wpel-link="internal">Slash Financial Raises $100 Million To Expand AI Banking Platform</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Slash Financial Reaches Unicorn Status With $100 Million Raise</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Slash Financial just pulled in $100 million in its Series C, with Ribbit Capital leading the way. Now, the company’s worth sits at $1.4 billion—officially making it a fintech unicorn. Khosla Ventures and Goodwater Capital were right there too, pitching in alongside Ribbit. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Plus, longtime backers like New Enterprise Associates and Y Combinator showed up for another round. Altogether, Slash has now raised over $160 million. The past two years have been a bit of a rocket ride for them—revenue shot up from $10 million to an eye-popping $250 million, annualized.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company’s growth reflects rising demand for modern business banking systems. These systems combine payments, treasury and financial management tools. Slash is positioning itself as a unified financial operating platform.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The funding will support expansion into new industries and markets. It will also strengthen product development across its platform. The company aims to build deeper capabilities for modern business operations.</span></p>
<h2><b>Rapid Growth Driven By AI-Native Financial Infrastructure</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Slash is on a roll. In 2025, its annual revenue shot past $250 million. That&#8217;s not all—within just nine months, it handled over $1 billion in stablecoin payments. Right now, the platform processes more than $30 billion in payments per year. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More than 5,000 businesses rely on Slash, from e-commerce and healthcare to crypto and a whole range of service-based industries. The company focuses on digital-first businesses with high transaction velocity. These businesses require flexible and scalable financial tools. Slash provides integrated solutions tailored to their operational needs.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Growth has been supported by its vertical expansion strategy. The company targets one industry at a time before scaling further. This approach helps build strong trust within each segment. Slash also benefits from AI-driven operational efficiency. Investors highlighted its strong output relative to team size. This reflects broader trends in AI-native fintech platforms.</span></p>
<h2><b>Twin AI Agent Introduces Automated Financial Operations<br />
</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_200103" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200103" class="size-full wp-image-200103" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/create-a-futuristic-neon-lit-visualizati_h_jAPdj7Sxy5MOXZoZkJMw_DS0hNs7mQEmZgKvmXuHOCA.png" alt="AI financial agent automating payments, invoices, and treasury operations through real-time data and secure workflows." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-200103" class="wp-caption-text">Slash’s Twin AI agent enables autonomous financial operations, streamlining workflows and replacing manual processes across business systems. Source: Created by Ventureburn</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Slash is launching its most advanced product to date called Twin. The system is an AI-powered financial agent designed to automate workflows. It acts as a central control layer across business financial activities. Twin functions like an AI Chief of Staff for financial operations. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">It uses real-time data across accounts, payments and treasury systems. It can execute tasks directly without manual input. Businesses can use Twin to manage payments and generate invoices. It can also create cards and handle reimbursements automatically. This removes the need for manual dashboard interaction.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The system introduces a shift toward autonomous financial operations. Instead of managing tools, users delegate actions to an intelligent agent. This improves speed and operational efficiency. Security remains a core feature within the platform. Twin operates through a secure agent layer that protects sensitive data. This ensures compliance while enabling automation.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company believes this model reflects the future of financial management. AI agents will replace manual workflows across business systems. Slash aims to lead this transition within fintech.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: <a href="https://ventureburn.com/cadence-ai-robotics-expansion/" data-wpel-link="internal">Cadence Expands AI And Robotic Partnerships With Nvidia And Google Cloud</a></span></p>
<h2><b>Expansion Strategy Builds Long-Term Market Position</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Slash was founded in 2021 and has evolved rapidly since launch. It initially focused on niche markets such as sneaker reselling. Early success in this segment helped validate its platform. The company faced a major setback in 2022 following market disruptions. Revenue dropped sharply after changes in the sneaker resale ecosystem. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Slash responded by shifting to a vertical banking model. This strategy focuses on building depth within specific industries. It then expands into new sectors once trust is established. This approach has driven consistent growth across different markets.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Today, Slash serves a wide range of industries including crypto and e-commerce. It also supports contractors, agencies and healthcare suppliers. This diversification strengthens its long-term resilience.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company’s platform combines multiple financial services into one system. These include banking, payments, treasury and expense management. Stablecoin support also adds flexibility for digital businesses.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The new funding will accelerate product development and expansion. It will also support continued <a href="https://ideascale.com/blog/what-is-innovation/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external">innovation</a> in AI-driven financial tools. Slash aims to become the financial backbone for modern businesses.</span></p>
